node.text:
Family Goals 🦁 what a wonderful sight of a lion family, otherwise known as a "pride".

While all other big cats are solitary by @nature, lions are the ones who live together, they are sociable and live in a group called pride.

Tag someone you would love to witness this in real life ❤️

📽 @safari.frank @franksteenhuisen
📍 Chobe National Park, Botswana
🎶 Circle Of Life - Carmen Twillie, Lebo M.

node.text:
Waterproof boy 🦎

📽 @simplygecko.co

This is a really cool aspect of gecko skin. The water is not actually touching their scales, but is coming into contact with air that is trapped in between tiny hair follicles called spinules. These follicles suspend the water so they can't flatten out over the surface area of the skin. They are less than a thousandth of a millimeter apart, and make geckos almost waterproof.
